Preheat your oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @potatoes{600%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then into 1cm chips (peeling
optional). Pop onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}.

Toss with half the @harissa spice mix{1%sachet}, @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to
taste}, and a drizzle of @oil{to taste}. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn
the #tray{} halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

In a large #bowl{}, combine the @Irish beef mince{240%g}, @Middle Eastern
spice mix{1%sachet}, @breadcrumbs{1%pack}, @water{2%tbsp} and @salt{1/4%tsp}.

> Double both for 4p.

Season with @pepper{to taste} and mix together by hand.

Roll into evenly-sized balls, then shape into 2cm thick burgers, one per person.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

> TIP: Burgers will shrink a little during cooking.

Place a large pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, add the burgers and fry until browned on the outside and cooked
through, ~{12-14%minutes}. Carefully turn every ~{3-4%minutes}, lowering the
heat if needed.

> IMPORTANT: Burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @prawns{180%g}.

Place a #pot{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, fry the prawns and remaining @harissa spice mix{1%sachet} until cooked
through, ~{3-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw prawns. Prawns are
> cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Remove the pot from the heat. Crumble in half the @Greek style cheese{50%g}.

Stir in the @sweet chilli sauce{1%sachet}, @mayo{2%sachet} and @sugar{1%tsp}.

> Double for 4p.

Taste and season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Trim the @salad leaves{120%g}. Reserve one leaf per burger.

Halve the remainder lengthways and thinly slice widthways.

In a #salad bowl{}, crumble the remaining @Greek style cheese{50%g} and mix well
with a drizzle of @oil{to taste} and @sugar{1/2%tsp}.

> Double for 4p.

Toss the chopped salad leaves through the dressing just before serving. Season
to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Pop the @brioche buns{2} into the oven to warm through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

== Assembly ==

To assemble the burgers, spread the harissa prawns over the base bun.

Top with a reserved salad leaf and then your burger.

Sandwich closed with the top bun.

Serve with chips and salad alongside.

Finish the salad with a drizzle of @balsamic glaze{1%sachet}.